  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The LINK program will connect vulnerable and marginalized communities to state and non-state services in Ankara, Gaziantep Sanliurfa and Adana provinces. LINK will be implemented by WATAN and Kirkayak, both Turkish NGOs, as well as GOAL. In addition GOAL will provide technical assistance, monitoring and evaluation and overall coordination. The main activity of LINK is the provision of Individual Protection Assistance (IPA). LINK will develop detailed district wide service maps and will facilitate households registration with DGMM and access to services for health, education and protection. Partners will closely coordinate with the Protection Cluster to ensure consistency with other actors using IPA. LINK will establish strong relationships with government services at both the district and provincial level to ensure refugees access services efficiently and effectively.WATAN will implement LINK in urban districts in Ankara. WATAN&apos;s previous experience in the city will help them identify vulnerable households to support via IPA and with psycho-social services. WATAN will also provide outreach to refugee households.Kirkayak will implement LINK in Gaziantep and Sanliurfa until 31 August 2020&#xA0;targeting the Syrian Semi-nomadic groups whom are marginalized and often excluded from services. GOAL will take over this implementation from 1 June 2019 in addition to rolling out LINK in Adana. In the second half of the program, experiences in working with the Syrian semi-nomadic population will be shared with state and non-state actors, mobilizing actors to incorporate them into their programming.Over 26&#xA0;months LINK will facilitate individuals&apos; connection to services, educate on protection threats and rights, provide psycho-social services, and implement an advocacy campaign.</narrative>
  </description>
